                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14549203" author="ndimiduk" created="Mon, 18 May 2015 20:51:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Counter per &lt;em&gt;row&lt;/em&gt;? That sounds like a bug, or someone assumed wide rows only.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We&apos;re generating counter names dynamically &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=jmspaggi&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;jmspaggi&quot;&gt;Jean-Marc Spaggiari&lt;/a&gt;? How do you think we should handle this? Option to specify what we&apos;re counting maybe &amp;#8211; count rows or count specific column occurrences in rows or found unique column names?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14549211" author="jmspaggi" created="Mon, 18 May 2015 20:56:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Exactly. Very good for very wide tables with only few rows. You can still increase the maximum number of counters but it become crazy quickly.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
            context.getCounter(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;QL_VERSIONS&quot;&lt;/span&gt;, currentRowKey + separator +
              thisRowQualifierName).increment(1);
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It creates one counter per row using the rowkey as the name to give you how many cells and versions there is per row. It&apos;s still useful in some cases, but generally speaking it creates to many counters...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think we should &quot;simply&quot; add an option to not count per row, but only per table, so just add a parameter and an if before this line.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14549826" author="lhofhansl" created="Tue, 19 May 2015 05:46:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;What the... This seems wrong. I do not think anybody wants this, we should remove it, and replace the code with a per total counter. Not a fan of a new option to keep senseless existing behavior.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14550735" author="jmspaggi" created="Tue, 19 May 2015 16:35:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;But might be nice to be able to count for a range of rows. Provide startkey / endkey then, instead of adding an option to disable that. If you don&apos;t specify them, we count just for the entire table. If you specify a range, we provide details per row for the range.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Make sense?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14625135" author="apurtell" created="Mon, 13 Jul 2015 18:40:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I agree with Lars. We shouldn&apos;t try to support broken behavior. Sometimes we make mistakes and need to rip them out.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15274602" author="ghelmling" created="Fri, 6 May 2016 19:27:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-15773&quot; title=&quot;CellCounter improvements&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-15773&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-15773&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
